### TL;DR Answer to Your Two Questions

| Question | Answer |
|----------|--------|
| **How do I get messages from the client after I subscribe?** | Use `esp_matter::client::interaction::subscribe::send_request()` with a custom `ReadClient::Callback`. The callback’s `OnAttributeData()` receives the TLV‑encoded attribute value (the contact sensor’s `BooleanState::StateValue`). Decode the boolean and act on it (open/close the shade). |
| **How can I reject a binding entry that I don’t want?** | Install a **user‑callback** on the `Binding::Bind` command (`command::set_user_callback`). Decode the incoming `Binding::Target` TLV, check `clusterId`, `attributeId`, optionally query the remote’s `Descriptor::DeviceTypeList` or enforce “one sensor only”. Return `ESP_ERR_NOT_SUPPORTED`, `ESP_ERR_INVALID_ARG`, etc. The SDK turns the error into a Matter status and the controller sees the bind request fail. |

